headline: Why Target Stock Is Up for 10 Straight Days—and What Comes Next
summary: Target  stock achieved its longest winning streak in more than seven years on Tuesday afternoon.  Just don’t take the rally as a sign that the retailer’s business is thriving.  Target shares have risen for 10 consecutive days, gaining about 8.8% through the period, according to Dow Jones Market Data.
